{{Canceled|reference books}}
'''''The Essential Guide to Episode I''''' was a planned trade paperback [[Star Wars: Essential Guides|Essential Guide]] that would cover the events, characters, and background of [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']]. It was to be written by [[Daniel Wallace|Dan Wallace]], and at one point was renamed '''''The Ultimate Guide to Episode I'''''. The guide was canceled when it became clear that the market for Episode I related products was long over, and that [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']], [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']] and [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] material such as the Clone Wars multimedia project and the ''[[New Jedi Order]]'' would contribute more material than could be covered in a single book. Thus the decision was made to relaunch the Essential Guide series, beginning with ''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]'' in [[2002]]. That book, along with ''[[The New Essential Guide to Vehicles and Vessels]]'', ''[[The New Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]'', ''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]'' and ''[[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species]]'' are among the books that have included information planned for this book.<ref name="LW">{{Blog|danwallace|34|Lostwords: The Essential Guide to Episode I}}</ref>

